21/08/2003
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Serbia-Montenegro scored an important victory against Wales in their Group Nine European Championship qualifier on Wednesday (20 August). 
The team now has a chance of getting into next year's finals if it beats Italy at home and Wales in Cardiff. 
About 20 friendly games were played across Europe on Wednesday. 
Macedonia beat Albania 3-1 in Skopje, while Croatia lost 3-1 to England in Ipswich. 
Moldova had no success against Turkey, which won 2-0, and Bulgaria defeated Lithuania in Sofia by a score of 3-1. 
Romania won 2-0 at home against Ukraine. 
(AP, AFP, Reuters - 20/08/03)
